<h2>Business Policies</h2>
<br>
<h4>Cost</h4>
<p>The cost of your product is how much it costs to produce (the raw materials and packaging plus labour) plus a contribution towards the overheads of the business. Hereâ€™s how to calculate that overhead contribution:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Estimate how many products we will sell in a year.</li>
    <li>Work out our total fixed costs - overheads plus drawings.</li>
    <li>Divide the total fixed costs by the number of units we expect to sell to calculate how much fixed costs to allocate to each unit.</li>
    <li>Add the direct costs for that unit to calculate the total product cost per item.</li>
</ol>
<br>

<h4>Shipping</h4>
<p>
    For deliveries within the contiguous United States, shipping options are standard, 2-day and overnight delivery. Our deliveries may contain a combination of FedEx and US Mail using the SmartPost service.
    Standard Shipping via Fed Ex Ground Service within the contiguous United States is divided into two types of serv");
